Coca - Cola sees worldwide case volume rising . Coca - Cola Co said Thursday that it expects worldwide unit case volume to increase by about 10 percent in the fourth quarter . For the full year , the company said it expects worldwide unit case volume to rise by about eight percent . The company ' s estimates placed its Latin American Group leading the growth with a 14 to 15 percent increase in fourth quarter unit case volume , followed by a 12 to 13 percent increase in the Africa Group . Fourth quarter unit case volume should increase five to six percent in the North America Group , 10 to 11 percent in Greater Europe and 11 to 12 percent in the Middle and Far East , the company said . Coca - Cola said worldwide gallon sales should rise 11 to 12 percent for the quarter and about seven percent for the year . 
